    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p> <p>Drain the <strong>tofu</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper<br /><br />Cut the <strong>dried tofu</strong> into cubes</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-chinese-tofu-and-broccoli-noodles/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p> <p>Once hot, add the <strong>tofu cubes</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until browned all over</p> <p>Once browned all over, remove the pan from the heat and add the<strong> soy sauce</strong> and give everything a good mix up until the tofu has absorbed the soy sauce</p> <p>Transfer to a plate and reserve the pan</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-chinese-tofu-and-broccoli-noodles/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, deseed the <strong>R</strong><strong><strong>omano</strong> pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into small bite-sized pieces</p> <p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) the <strong>garlic</strong>\u00a0</p> <p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-chinese-tofu-and-broccoli-noodles/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium heat</p> <p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped Romano pepper</strong>,<strong> sliced garlic </strong>and<strong> chopped ginger</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until starting to soften</p> <p>\u00a0</p> <p>\u00a0</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-chinese-tofu-and-broccoli-noodles/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>broccoli</strong> into small<span class=\"text-highlight\"> florets and</span> discard the stem</p> <p>Add the <strong>wholewheat noodles</strong> to a pot and cover with <strong>boiled water</strong> until fully submerged</p> <p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for an initial 2-3 min</p> <p>After 2-3 min, add the <strong>broccoli florets</strong> and cook for 3-4 min further or\u00a0until tender with a slight bite, then drain and return\u00a0<span class=\"text-highlight\">everything</span> to the pan</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-chinese-tofu-and-broccoli-noodles/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>miso paste</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>hoisin <span class=\"text-highlight\">sauce</span></strong>\u00a0and <strong>cayenne <span class=\"text-highlight\">pepper</span></strong> (Can't handle the heat? Go easy!) with 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013\u00a0this is your<strong> spicy sauce</strong></p> <p>Once softened, return the <strong>tofu</strong> to the pan with the <strong>spicy sauce</strong> and cook for 2-3 min further or until thick and rich</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-chinese-tofu-and-broccoli-noodles/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, trim, then slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p> <p>Stir\u00a0the <strong>toasted\u00a0sesame oil</strong> through the <strong>drained noodles</strong> and <strong>broccoli</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-chinese-tofu-and-broccoli-noodles/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>spicy Chinese tofu</strong> over the<strong> noodles</strong> and <strong>broccoli</strong> and garnish with the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong></p> <p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
